Piemaster
Can someone run through me the advantages and disadvantages of grouping please.


Advantages:

- Less HP lost and so less downtime
- Ability to do areas missions earlier than you would be able to comfortably do solo.
- Dinoz can compensate for each other's weaknesses somewhat.


Disadvantages:

- Entire group are forced to wait when one of the them runs out og HP
- Obviously they all have to do the same areas/quests at the same time which may not be optimal according to the dinoz strengths, weaknesses and needs.
- Some key fights can only be done solo anyway.
- Certain skill (such as flight) are severely weakened when grouping.


Gold doesn't seem to make much difference. XP can be higher or lower depending on the situation, or so it seems to me anyway.
On december 3, 2009
[None]
Can someone run through me the advantages and disadvantages of grouping please

Advantages
Each Dinoz in a group will take less damage than it would if it was solo

If one Dinoz dies, the rest of the group can complete certain quests or move to the next area (dead Dinoz can be revived using a potion in the new area)

A group can complete a mission long before a solo Dinoz could do the same mission (remember that each Dinoz needs to complete each step of the mission - i.e. talk to person with each Dinoz in turn at each step)

Gold seems to be more plentiful in a group (especially if you have a Napadino equipped) - I may be imagining this and I have no actual data but it seems I get more gold in groups.

Disadvantages
Possibly harder to progress in the game because you must buy one potion for each Dinoz in the group to get an extra turn (so if you want to rush something like getting the pearl it is easier (or at least cheaper) to do this with a powerful solo Dinoz than a group)

XP from combat is split between the group so each Dinoz receives XP more slowly (this is balanced by having to rest or be healed less) - XP from validating missions is received in full by each Dinoz.

Missions which involve a lot of fighting (e.g. Wolf Hunting) take longer to complete as a group than solo since only one Dinoz receives the credit for the kills. (partly balanced by taking less damage and therefore having to rest less)

It is much easier to forget to use collecting skills each turn because you only need to move a group leader.
